SUMMARY:Bat Chat
DTSTAMP:20260618T044224Z
DTSTART:20260619T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Stroll to Waugh Drive Bridge for a Bat Chat with the Houston Ar
	ea Bat Team and see the bat colony up close! \nDid you know? These populat
	ion of Mexican Free-tailed Bats at the Waugh Bridge can reach a peak of ap
	proximately 300\,000 in the summer months! Around sunset\, the colony leav
	es the crevices beneath the bridge and create a whirlwind-like formation a
	s they emerge. Join the Houston Area Bat Team to learn and discover as the
	y share fun\, educational facts and insights about these miniature\, flyin
	g mammals! \nInvite your family and friends\, bring a picnic blanket\, wea
	r your bug spray\, and admire this unique phenomena. \n\n\n\nBat Chats are
	 held every Friday evening from May to August as part of our Summer Specie
	s series\, starting 30 minutes before sunset. \n  \nCost\nFree \nTime\n7:3
	0 – 8:30pm (30 minutes before sunset) \nMeeting Location\nWaugh Bridge Bat
	 Colony Observation Deck (along Allen Parkway) \nREGISTRATION\n\nhttps://b
	uffalobayou.org/event/2026-june-bat-chat-3/\n\nFrom Buffalo Bayou Partners
	hip
URL:https://buffalobayou.org/event/2026-june-bat-chat-3/
LOCATION:Waugh Drive Bat Bridge\, 1
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:buffalo-bayou-partnership
CATEGORIES:Buffalo Bayou Partnership
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H
END:VEVENT
